songs.title: 7AM
songs.lyrics:
[Intro]
It's 7 in the morning

[Verse 1]
You were rolling in the cash, yeah, you were rolling in bitches
And I was rolling in my Lincoln, I was a shitty waitress
And boy, you had me kinda thinking you were making me famous
And I was getting cozy with the thought of giving you kisses

[Pre-Chorus]
I was a fresh 18 (I've been such a good girl)
You call me while I sleep (get into my world)
You're making me phat beats (you've got the sound I'm lookin' for)
You're saying that you think I got star quality

[Chorus]
Got you stuck, stuck in my head (stuck in my)
Playing like a song in the back of my head (stuck in my)
How'd you get stuck, stuck, stuck in my head (stuck in my)
Playing like a song in the back of my head
It's 7 in the morning

[Verse 2]
Oh, it's 7 in the mornin' and I'm not even tired
Your voice is spinnin', screwing with my mind
Boy, you've got me wired
Put your hands all over me, on your synthesizer
I got this nasty crave, I need a drop of your tranquilizer

[Pre-Chorus]
I was a fresh 18 (I've been such a good girl)
You call me while I sleep (get into my world)
You're making me phat beats (you've got the sound I'm lookin' for)
You're saying that you think I got star quality

[Chorus]
Got you stuck, stuck in my head (stuck in my)
Playing like a song in the back of my head (stuck in my)
How'd you get stuck, stuck, stuck in my head (stuck in my)
Playing like a song in the back of my head
It's 7 in the morning

[Bridge]
I don't know what's wrong, I'm just not tired
And boy, I need a tranquilizer
I want you to come over (come get inspired)
And play me like your synthesizer

[Refrain]
You were rolling in the cash, yeah, you were rolling in bitches
And I was rolling in my Lincoln, I was a shitty waitress

[Chorus]
Got you stuck, stuck in my head (stuck in my)
Playing like a song in the back of my head (stuck in my)
How'd you get stuck, stuck, stuck in my head (stuck in my)
Playing like a song in the back of my head, it's 7 in the
Got you stuck, stuck in my head (stuck in my)
Playing like a song in the back of my head (stuck in my)
How'd you get stuck, stuck, stuck in my head (stuck in my)
Playing like a song in the back of my head
